<div class="api-section">
    <h2>💻 Under the Hood: Book Review API</h2>
    <p>
        SK@VNIT Books is powered by a robust RESTful API built with <strong>Node.js</strong> and <strong>Express.js</strong>. Here’s what makes our backend tick:
    </p>
    <ul class="api-list">
        <li><strong>POST /signup</strong> – Register a new user</li>
        <li><strong>POST /login</strong> – Authenticate and receive a JWT token</li>
        <li><strong>POST /books</strong> – Add a new book (for authenticated users)</li>
        <li><strong>GET /books</strong> – List all books with pagination and filters</li>
        <li><strong>GET /books/:id</strong> – View detailed book info, average rating, and reviews</li>
        <li><strong>POST /books/:id/reviews</strong> – Submit a review (one per user per book)</li>
        <li><strong>PUT /reviews/:id</strong> – Update your review</li>
        <li><strong>DELETE /reviews/:id</strong> – Delete your review</li>
        <li><strong>GET /search</strong> – Search books by title or author</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        <em>Built with security, performance, and user experience in mind!</em>
    </p>
